    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera, featuring the 3.6L M96.03 naturally aspirated flat-six. This specimen is mechanically pristine, featuring a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a dry rear main seal. Power is managed via a G96 six-speed manual transaxle, offering crisp synchronization and short-throw precision. The chassis retains its factory-spec torsional rigidity, supported by a multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts that deliver telepathic steering feedback. The Arctic Silver Metallic finish shows exceptional depth with no evidence of thermal cycling on the engine components or oxidation on the undercarriage. A turn-key enthusiast example with a linear torque curve and flawless stoichiometric balance.",
