      "description": "Available is an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3, a superlative example of the E46 chassis. The S54 3.2L straight-six features a factory-perfect power band, with documented VANOS solenoid servicing and rod bearing prophylaxis already completed. The drivetrain utilizes the sought-after 6-speed Getrag manual transmission, paired with a variable M-differential lock for optimal torque distribution. Mechanically, the vehicle is beyond reproach: the rear subframe has been structurally reinforced, and the suspension retains its original kinematics with refreshed OEM bushings and dampers. Every individual throttle body (ITB) is synchronized for razor-sharp throttle response. This is a turn-key specimen for the collector who demands mechanical perfection and atmospheric induction purity.",
